{"body": "I looked into this and `ActiveRecord::ConnectionAdapters::ConnectionManagement` does not appear to initiate a connection to the db if one doesn't already exist. Unfortunately `ActiveRecord::QueryCache` does initiate a connection. Right now if I skip `ActiveRecord::QueryCache` and `ActiveRecord::Migration::CheckPending` in my app, then i can get the homepage to load with no errors.\r\n\r\nRegardless of other middleware requiring database access, this one should not. Even if this does not full eliminate the problem, it is a required step on the way to fully solving the larger issue. ", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/19223074", "created_at": "2013-06-10T20:10:05Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/10792#issuecomment-19223074", "updated_at": "2013-06-10T20:10:05Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 10792, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/schneems", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/db953d125f5cc49756edb6149f1b813e?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F6ef42a6eab211ddd71ac423a80b42d15.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/received_events", "gravatar_id": "db953d125f5cc49756edb6149f1b813e", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "schneems", "type": "User", "id": 59744, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237dbb5bd3543c1510088c0"}, "id": 19223074, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repo